WEBVTT

1
00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:36.470
Check this out, Sasaki.

2
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.470
Apparently, the brand of cigarettes 
someone smokes says a lot about them.

3
00:01:41.430 --> 00:01:42.730
What's this about?

4
00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:46.400
It's the smoke brand personality test.

5
00:01:46.400 --> 00:01:50.610
This stuff really gets the young'uns 
going during drinking parties.

6
00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:52.240
What does it say about me?

7
00:01:52.820 --> 00:01:57.240
"Straightforward and devoted, 
will never cheat," it says!

8
00:01:59.240 --> 00:02:03.500
It also says, 
"Oblivious and socially inept."

9
00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:08.130
Hey! You didn't have to read that part!

10
00:02:08.130 --> 00:02:09.420
Read the room!

11
00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:15.180
A popular topic among the youth, huh?

12
00:02:22.680 --> 00:02:25.560
Oh, yeah, that stuff.

13
00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:28.020
You knew about it?

14
00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:29.570
Just that it exists.

15
00:02:29.570 --> 00:02:32.860
But those things usually...

16
00:02:32.860 --> 00:02:34.320
A coworker told me about it,

17
00:02:34.700 --> 00:02:37.110
and I thought it sounded fun.

18
00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:41.950
A'ight, let's check it out.

19
00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:45.250
What's it say about you, Sasaki-san?

20
00:02:45.710 --> 00:02:50.590
Erm... there it is. It says...

21
00:02:51.380 --> 00:02:55.260
"Tends to be a masochist despite 
otherwise looking down on others."

22
00:02:56.590 --> 00:02:57.970
What in the world?

23
00:02:57.970 --> 00:03:00.930
Stop that... Let me smoke.

24
00:03:00.930 --> 00:03:01.850
For real.

25
00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:05.680
Wh-What was your result?

26
00:03:08.520 --> 00:03:12.070
"Two-faced, with a surprisingly 
high sex drive."

27
00:03:13.980 --> 00:03:18.450
These things usually bring up 
sex stuff as a punchline.

28
00:03:18.450 --> 00:03:21.700
And you can see right through 
the creator's prejudices.

29
00:03:23.790 --> 00:03:27.160
Funny how it was totally right 
about one thing, though.

30
00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:32.670
I apologize.

31
00:03:34.340 --> 00:03:36.800
Huh? What are you kneeling for?

32
00:03:37.130 --> 00:03:39.390
Where'd your cigarette and glasses go?

33
00:03:40.930 --> 00:03:46.680
I'm really sorry for unknowingly 
bringing up such an awkward topic...

34
00:03:47.480 --> 00:03:49.100
and for making you say that out loud.

35
00:03:55.360 --> 00:03:56.400
I mean,

36
00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:59.860
yeah, I do hate dirty talk.

37
00:04:00.950 --> 00:04:05.330
But I know you only brought it up 
thinking the youth found it fun.

38
00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:12.170
You did it for me but ended up 
apologizing for it anyway.

39
00:04:13.880 --> 00:04:15.800
Way to make yourself 
look silly, Sasaki-san.

40
00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:24.850
I'm not mad at you, okay? 
Get back to smoking.

41
00:04:24.850 --> 00:04:26.060
Tayama-san...

42
00:04:26.390 --> 00:04:29.730
It might actually be right 
about you being two-faced.

43
00:04:31.310 --> 00:04:35.440
I've been thinking it for a while, 
but I had trouble putting it into words.

44
00:04:36.070 --> 00:04:37.940
But I get it now.

45
00:04:41.820 --> 00:04:44.200
You act all aloof, but you're really nice!

46
00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:46.910
That's exactly the kind of person you are!

47
00:04:55.540 --> 00:04:56.710
Tayama-san?

48
00:04:58.170 --> 00:05:00.970
You were about to smoke 
that one earlier, right?

49
00:05:00.970 --> 00:05:03.470
Oh, yeah, thanks?

50
00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:05.850
Right, sorry.

51
00:05:05.850 --> 00:05:07.600
I completely forgot.

52
00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:10.350
Want me to light it for you, too?

53
00:05:13.020 --> 00:05:15.730
D-Did I do something to make you mad?

54
00:05:15.730 --> 00:05:18.650
I'm not mad. Just look 
at my thousand-watt smile.

55
00:05:29.950 --> 00:05:32.330
L-Let me say I'm sorry anyway.

56
00:05:32.330 --> 00:05:33.580
What're you apologizing for?

57
00:05:43.430 --> 00:05:48.760
In the end, I just left after making 
Tayama-san upset last night.

58
00:05:51.600 --> 00:05:53.140
Thank you! Come again!

59
00:05:56.150 --> 00:06:00.150
Should a guy like me really be lining up 
at Yamada-san's register?

60
00:06:00.780 --> 00:06:01.900
No way.

61
00:06:05.070 --> 00:06:06.530
Sir.

62
00:06:07.030 --> 00:06:10.540
Please step this way. 
I can ring you up now.

63
00:06:10.830 --> 00:06:12.540
R-Right.

64
00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:28.300
Oh?

65
00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:33.730
Something funny happened 
between those two, huh?

66
00:06:33.730 --> 00:06:35.390
Wish I could've seen it.

67
00:07:00.790 --> 00:07:01.590
Man...

68
00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:05.920
We're sorry for making you 
come all the way in this heat.

69
00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:08.300
Oh, don't mention it.

70
00:07:08.300 --> 00:07:10.180
Please have this tea.

71
00:07:12.260 --> 00:07:13.520
I'll do just that.

72
00:07:13.520 --> 00:07:14.640
Go for it.

73
00:07:18.770 --> 00:07:23.650
The proposal you sent over 
really helped us out.

74
00:07:23.650 --> 00:07:28.240
Our owner was over the moon, saying, 
"You can always count on Genki Trading!"

75
00:07:28.490 --> 00:07:29.870
I'm glad to hear it.

76
00:07:29.870 --> 00:07:31.410
Good afternoon, everyone.

77
00:07:31.410 --> 00:07:35.330
We've had a string of summer-like 
days since the start of May.

78
00:07:36.250 --> 00:07:39.370
We've already switched over 
to business casual.

79
00:07:39.670 --> 00:07:42.420
That's wonderful.

80
00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:45.880
We aren't allowed to 
until summer's actually here.

81
00:07:46.630 --> 00:07:48.510
That sounds rough.

82
00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:51.010
In northern Japan, 
the entirety of tomorrow...

83
00:07:51.010 --> 00:07:53.930
Anyway, we're counting on you.

84
00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:55.270
Thank you very much.

85
00:07:55.970 --> 00:07:58.640
What's next on your schedule? 
Back to the office for more work?

86
00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:01.100
No, I think I can head 
straight home today.

87
00:08:01.100 --> 00:08:02.940
Glad to hear it.

88
00:08:02.940 --> 00:08:05.440
You're always working 
much too hard, Sasaki-san.

89
00:08:33.640 --> 00:08:37.980
I can't deal with how warm it is 
all the way until evening.

90
00:08:38.480 --> 00:08:41.900
If it's like this already, how much 
worse is summer going to get?

91
00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:51.070
That ice cream's good, huh?

92
00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:52.660
Yep!

93
00:08:53.120 --> 00:08:55.120
You did sweat a lot.

94
00:08:55.120 --> 00:08:55.910
So hot.

95
00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:59.120
Maybe I'll get some ice cream 
for the walk home.

96
00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:09.090
Of course it'd be crowded at this time.

97
00:09:10.130 --> 00:09:11.630
Wait, what?

98
00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:15.140
Y-Yamada-san?!

99
00:09:16.560 --> 00:09:19.430
She's working the evening shift today?

100
00:09:19.430 --> 00:09:21.690
What a lucky day!

101
00:09:21.690 --> 00:09:23.060
Thank you for shopping with us!

102
00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:27.860
H-H-H-Half sleeves?!

103
00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:29.780
I'll just update your point card.

104
00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:33.320
Oh, so they switched 
to the summer uniform!

105
00:09:33.320 --> 00:09:35.910
Such a refreshing look!

106
00:09:36.700 --> 00:09:38.910
And heck, Yamada-san's just so...

107
00:09:39.200 --> 00:09:40.450
so pr...

108
00:09:43.620 --> 00:09:46.000
Guess I don't need that ice cream anymore.

109
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:47.210
I'll just go.

110
00:09:56.720 --> 00:10:00.720
You left without shopping yesterday 
even though Yamada-san was there.

111
00:10:01.390 --> 00:10:02.350
Why?

112
00:10:06.060 --> 00:10:08.070
Were you watching again?

113
00:10:08.070 --> 00:10:12.110
Who wouldn't notice a tall dude 
hanging around the entrance?

114
00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:14.860
Oh, sorry. Was I a bother?

115
00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:18.370
So, why'd you do it?

116
00:10:22.540 --> 00:10:26.580
It was so hot yesterday, 
I started craving some ice cream.

117
00:10:26.580 --> 00:10:27.630
Yeah?

118
00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:32.670
But the store was such a low-cortisol 
zone that it cooled me down plenty.

119
00:10:32.670 --> 00:10:34.340
What does that even mean?

120
00:10:36.890 --> 00:10:42.390
And here I thought the sight of Yamada-san
in short sleeves blew the heat away.

121
00:10:43.680 --> 00:10:46.060
Ow! Hot!

122
00:10:46.310 --> 00:10:48.020
Bingo, huh?

123
00:10:48.020 --> 00:10:49.560
No, no, not at all!

124
00:10:52.780 --> 00:10:57.700
Retail workers like Yamada-san switch 
uniforms to herald the changing seasons.

125
00:10:57.700 --> 00:10:59.240
All I have for them is gratitude—

126
00:10:59.240 --> 00:11:01.330
You didn't find it pretty, then?

127
00:11:01.330 --> 00:11:02.580
I did not say that!

128
00:11:12.300 --> 00:11:16.130
I do believe short sleeves 
suit her very well.

129
00:11:17.130 --> 00:11:19.430
You're sweating buckets.

130
00:11:19.430 --> 00:11:21.470
I mean, it's pretty hot today.

131
00:11:23.390 --> 00:11:24.640
Huh...

132
00:11:25.600 --> 00:11:28.940
Aren't you hot in that jacket?

133
00:11:28.940 --> 00:11:32.980
I'm dressed lightly underneath. 
Nothing compared to you.

134
00:11:32.980 --> 00:11:34.990
Oh, you are?

135
00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:36.070
Yeah.

136
00:11:38.450 --> 00:11:39.240
Check it out.

137
00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:42.990
T-Tayama-san, uh...

138
00:11:42.990 --> 00:11:44.120
I'm sorry.

139
00:11:46.620 --> 00:11:49.000
I'm sorry for looking at your belly!

140
00:11:49.540 --> 00:11:50.790
You know...

141
00:11:54.380 --> 00:11:56.380
Doesn't your belly feel cold like that?

142
00:11:59.430 --> 00:12:00.970
Doesn't your belly feel cold like that?

143
00:12:00.970 --> 00:12:02.470
Doesn't your belly feel cold like that?

144
00:12:02.470 --> 00:12:03.390
...like that?

145
00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:04.220
...like that?

146
00:12:04.220 --> 00:12:05.640
...that? ...that? ...that?

147
00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.270
How wonderful!

148
00:12:09.560 --> 00:12:10.850
Yay.

149
00:12:11.400 --> 00:12:13.650
Aren't you cold? Are you sure about this?

150
00:12:19.400 --> 00:12:22.370
I swear, this geezer...

151
00:12:24.530 --> 00:12:25.490
Tayama-san?

152
00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:28.000
Use this if you'd like.

153
00:12:28.870 --> 00:12:31.040
The night breeze still gets chilly.

154
00:12:35.380 --> 00:12:38.880
Oh, if you'd rather not, that's fine.

155
00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:39.800
Huh?

156
00:12:40.430 --> 00:12:44.760
Sorry, Tayama-san, I meant 
to use it to cover your belly.

157
00:12:44.760 --> 00:12:46.890
I wasn't telling you to wear it!

158
00:12:46.890 --> 00:12:48.430
That'd make you uncomfortable...

159
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:49.810
Wouldn't it?

160
00:12:52.810 --> 00:12:55.110
Uh, Tayama-san?

161
00:13:02.320 --> 00:13:04.570
Shut it, arm man.

162
00:13:04.570 --> 00:13:06.580
A-Arm man...?

163
00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:08.910
Blep.

164
00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:16.880
I don't get it. What does 
she mean, "arm man"?

165
00:13:29.470 --> 00:13:33.980
This must be what makes me dense.

166
00:13:43.320 --> 00:13:47.580
Sasaki likes arms more than 
he does bellies, huh?

167
00:13:54.170 --> 00:13:57.210
I should lay off the ramen for a while.
